Cell["Optical Binding Simulation", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.966498873232978*^9, 
  3.9664988768485003`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9356f2c9-3543-41b1-aa9e-\
f2f01b2916a9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The goal of this notebook is to attempt to establish how to calculate \
optical forces while using Einstein summation notation to make it easier to \
code in Python. First we will start by rederiving the conventional dyadics \
Greens function.  \n\n",
